  "text": [
    "My embarrassment at his nakedness,",
    "at the pool\u2019s edge,",
    "and my wife, with his,",
    "standing, watching\u2014",
    "this was a freedom",
    "not given me who am",
    "more naked,",
    "less contained",
    "by my own white flesh",
    "and the ability",
    "to take quietly",
    "what comes to me.",
    "The sense of myself",
    "separate, grew",
    "a white mirror",
    "in the quiet water",
    "he breaks with his hands",
    "and feet, kicking,",
    "pulls up to land",
    "on the edge by the feet",
    "of these women",
    "who must know",
    "that for each",
    "man is a speech",
    "describes him, makes",
    "the day grow white",
    "and sure, a quietness of water",
    "in the mind,",
    "lets hang, descriptive",
    "as a risk, something",
    "for which he cannot find",
    "a means or time."
  ],
  "title": "The Pool",
